column5: I just want to say it was nice knowing everyone here in my OFC family,today I noticed something very disturbing to me. The Mayans were totally wrong I was not scared about there prediction as they have been way off before but this is the end of the world as my musky hunter calendar ends today.  Happy New Years every one
LMAO! Happy new years to you too.
Why would anyone want to catch a MUSTY Fish.....  HAPPY REDNECK NEW YEARS   Bob
Hahahaha, good one Mike, Happy New Year to you and your family
Happy New Year Mike........all the best for good health much good fortune and of course good Muskie hunting in 2013.
Happy New Year to you & yours too Mike.   See you on LSC in about 10 months
We just found a new calander , looks like we're good to go ..... lol Happy New Years ..........
Skipp are you sure it's not gona end? It might be them carp or salmon guys messing with you I have not seen a 2013 calendar yet
LOL Mike  Right back at ya and hope I get to see ya more than once in 13

Relax, the latest archaeological research indicates that once the musky hunter calendar ends it simply begins anew, but those who follow it are now required to target rock bass for the duration of the next calendar. I think it's carp after that...

For sure Phil we need to get you and Pj up here in July.  Dave I think I'm gonna look funny tossing 10" lures targeting rock bass but he there is no season on them so this might be a good thing. If a CO asks me why I'm fishing musky OOS I will just pull out my phone bring this thread up and inform him I'm after rock bass but these pesky musky keep bugging me
Holy Crap Mike,  DON"T DO THAT TO ME!!!  LMAO, you had me going for a bit there!  Here's to the New Year everyone!  Cheers, Ron....
Don't forget to print out a calendar as evidence.
Get a new calendar and get back on the muskie horse Mike.  Big fish 2013... here ya come!
